
Introduction to the N-body problem using NagBody codes
Mario A. Rodriguez-Meza

Numerical codes list:

I. Sources and installation command (you must be in NagBody_pkg directory:
(Remember to execute: make -f NagBody install_dirs to create several necessary directories)

Gravitation, add names below to: NagBody_sources/gravitation/
1. nbody_n2		: make -f NagBody install_nbody_n2
2. model		: make -f NagBody install_model
3. gbsph		: make -f NagBody install_gbsph
4. analysis_grav	: make -f NagBody install_analysis_grav
5. analysis_galaxy	: make -f NagBody install_analysis_galaxy
7. galaxy_starscream	: make -f NagBody install_galaxy_starscream


Cmplxfluids, , add names below to: NagBody_sources/cmplxfluids/
1. md_blj_n2		: make -f NagBody install_
2. analysis_md		: make -f NagBody install_
3. md_blj		: make -f NagBody install_
4. md_ic_model		: make -f NagBody install_


Gadget derived codes (Volker Springel codes)
9. gdgt207cluster	: make -f NagBody install_gdgt207cluster
10. gdgt207galaxy	: make -f NagBody install_gdgt207galaxy
11. gdgt207gassphere	: make -f NagBody install_gdgt207gassphere
12. gdgt207lcdm		: make -f NagBody install_gdgt207lcdm
13. n-genic		: make -f NagBody install_n-genic
14. galic		: make -f NagBody install_galic

COLA type of codes (Several authors)
1. cola			: make -f NagBody install_cola
2. plcola		: make -f NagBody install_plcola
3. mgplcola		: make -f NagBody install_mgplcola


Perturbations
1. mgpt			: make -f NagBody install_mgpt

CLASS type of codes (based on Julien Lesgourges team CLASS, HI_CLASS and Montepython)
1. class		: make -f NagBody install_class
2. hiclass		: make -f NagBody install_class
3. class_mgpt		: make -f NagBody install_class
4. hiclass_mgpt		: make -f NagBody install_class
5. montepython		: make -f NagBody install_montepython
6. planck2018		: make -f NagBody install_planck2018

Analysis cosmo codes (by several authors)
1. powmes		: make -f NagBody install_powmes
2. rockstar		: make -f NagBody install_


Templates
1. templateBessel	: make -f NagBody install_templateBessel

Visualization
1. nplot2d		: make -f NagBody install_nplot2d


II. To clean a code use:

make -f NagBody clean_CODENAME

where CODENAME is one of the code names above.


III. Readme install files are under directory Readmes, it is used the same directory structure.


IV. You can extract and pack an individual code using

$ make -f NagBody packing_CODENAME

The zip file is created in the zip directory.


V. Documentation of the numerical code are in the corresponding doc directory. There you will find man pages and/or docs and/or papers.

VI. Tests. In each of the individual directory there is a tests directory to try the corresponding code. In some cases there are initial conditions and parameters files, Jupiter notebooks or another material.
